Kiasha N wrote a review Aug 2018
North Riding, South Africa9 contributions10 helpful votes
Great view but noisy
The hotel is well situated opposite the beach. The hotel room was spacious and clean. We did not use the kitchen facilities. The restaurant staff did not understand what vegetarian meant though. The staff were friendly enough but seeing that it is a big hotel, you do not get that boutique hotel treatment. It is quite a busy hotel with people milling around the lobby at all times. In regards to the noise: We had a sea facing room, so the construction next door was not that noisy. There is however a beach concert held opposite the hotel. Of course this is not at the control of the hotel. The music does go on until late into the night. But if you are looking for some RnR like the American troops did at My Khe beach in the 70’s then this is not the place. Rather book at one of the…
Dear Kiasha N, Thank you so much for taking the time to share your feedback about your recent stay with us here at À La Carte Danang Beach. We are delighted to read how you enjoyed your stay in our resort. Please accept our sincere apologies that certain parts of the stay were not up to your expectations. We hope to have the opportunity to welcoming you back. Kind regards, À La Carte Team.
